The Jimmy Johns location in Iowa City is notoriously SLOW with delivery. A few weeks ago I ordered a sandwich and requested delivery as I needed to work over my lunch and had a 1:15pm meeting. I waited over an hour to receive my delivery. When I called to inquire about the sandwich the worker was less than apologetic and told me they were "just busy." Recently I received a "free sandwich" redemption code. I decided to give them another shot, since the sandwich was free. I ordered my sandwich at 11:43am and waited over 45 minutes for my delivery. My office is literally two blocks from the Jimmy Johns. However, I'm also told the customer service in-store is bad too. I think their management could do better at this location.

This had just happened. I ordered my Jimmy Johns sandwich at approximately 159AM. The guy that took my order said they would get to me ASAP. Great! I didn't want the delivery guy to wait for me since they seemed busy, so I went downstairs right away to the first floor of the dorm I live in. I waited for approximately 45 minutes with no word from them. I called them again to confirm that my order was on the way. The guy that picked up said that "it was PROBABLY on the way." Alright... So I waited for another 30 minutes. I got tired of waiting, so I called one final time, and it turned out, my order was voided for some reason?? At this point, I'm starving, so I'm pretty annoyed. Well what happened was, one of the employees inputed my phone number incorrectly, and as a result, they were contacting a different person who had nothing to do with my order. I did not get my sandwich unfortunately. The manager was pretty nice and professional about it, which I appreciated. This is why I gave a 2-star rating rather than a 1-star rating. I also ended up receiving 10$ dollars in store credit. I'm just disappointed that I wasted about 1.5 hours of my time for a very simple mistake they made. However, I realize that everyone makes mistakes, so I really hope they don't make this same mistake again. And I do really like Jimmy Johns sandwiches in general, but I am hesitant to order from this specific store location again.

This was horrible. I am a student who has been a huge fan of jimmy johns but today they lost all my love. A group of friends and I decided to take a quick study break, to get dinner. We ended up going to jimmy johns where one of my friends ordered a turkey sandwich without tomatoes. Instead he came back to our study area with a sandwich without any TURKEY. That is right a turkey sandwich WITHOUT turkey. We decided to call and tell the MANAGER about the situation. We requested they deliver  the same sandwich with turkey on it this time....It was raining and we felt it was a reasonable request. The MANAGER said she would have the sandwich on the way. Without asking for a number she hung up...RUDE. Keep in mind  this was a 10 min walk so maybe a 3min drive. After an HOUR, we called again. We ended up talking to the MANAGER again and she said she was sorry but the never got our number and THREW THE OTHER SANDWICH AWAY. They eventually brought the sandwich but honestly this is just not okay. Also we didn't get a refund nor any other form of compensation beside a bag of plain chips. PS They INSISTED on getting the other sandwich back! I know what you're thinking, but not this is not a joke, this happened.

This was the worst catering experience ever! I ordered our platter of 30 sandwiches, 30 bags of chips and 1 bucket of pickles 3 days prior to the delivery date. This should have been amble time to prepare an order of this size for delivery. On the evening of the party, we had requested the food be delivered at 7:15pm. Around 7:30pm, we called and they said it was ready to go but they were busy. The delivery driver finally showed up around 8pm with the sandwiches only...no chips and no pickles. He said he'd go back to get those items. The delivery driver came back with 20 chips and nothing else...we were still missing 10 bags of chips and a bucket of pickles. Upon calling the store and requesting to talk to a manager, the phone was put down and someone was yelling profanities about my husband "coming at him like that...". Another person picked up the phone and said they would apply a $20 credit to the account. That is simply not sufficient for the terrible service we received, not to mention a third of our order was paid for and not received. Tried to contact Corporate and they said it was sent to the store, but I have heard nothing!

I placed an order online while I waited in the lobby of the law school.  l received a confirmation order for my order at 5:57 PM, which was approximately 10 minutes I submitted my order.  As my phone was on silent, I missed the driver's call at 6:52 PM.  I called him back at 6:53 PM and the driver did not answer.  As my call when straight to his voicemail, he may have been trying to call me again.  I was still at the lobby door and I figured I would hold off on calling him back.  During this time I listened to his message which he said he "was just pulling up and asked that I "meet him out front."  After sitting waiting by the door for nearly ten minutes, I called him back and again he didn't answer.  Put aside the unfreakishly fast deliver for a minute.  If I order delivery, I don't want it delivered to the parking lot.  If I wanted to go outside, I would have gone and picked it up myself.  Not impressed.
